\subsection{Ablation Study of HMC Postulates with Significance}
We perform ablations by varying:
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
    \item P0 scaling ($d_{\rm mem}\propto \exp(c S_{\rm BH})$ with $c\in\{0.75,1,1.25\}$),
    \item Scrambling strength (weak vs nominal),
    \item Gentleness parameter $\varepsilon$.
\end{itemize}

We report metrics over 100 runs: residual final entropy, RMSE to the ideal Page curve, turnover step, and maximum $g^{(2)}$ deviation. Summary statistics are in Table~\ref{tab:ablation}, and Welch tests with FDR correction and effect sizes in Table~\ref{tab:ablation_stats}.

